# Validators
Manual action *needed*. We are doing a soft transition to Vision 4.0.6 over the coming week. The deadline for this is next Thursday 3pm UTC, at which time we'll be releasing our next soft update, so please make sure you complete the following in time! Please note; there will be no effect on Vtrust by switching over early, so please do it as soon as you can! 

Also, this new update should help address any issues where the validator just suddenly stops setting weights (Happening to OTF and Foundry), so would advise updating to combat that 🙂

### Orchestrator / GPU server 

First, the orchestrator (GPU) needs updating. You must be on a VM/bare metal for this - Runpod and vast are no longer supported (no docker in docker).

You can see the full instructions here!
https://github.com/namoray/vision-workers

If you already have a GPU setup, you need to first stop any curerntly running containers, and then do the following:

For autoupdates:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/namoray/vision-workers
cd vision-workers
git reset --hard origin/main
python3 run_autoupdates_validator.py
```
For manual:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/namoray/vision-workers
cd vision-workers
git fetch
git reset --hard origin/main
./launch_orchestrator.sh
```

### On the proxy 
Make sure you have configured the GPU first, and it's all up and running.

1. **Edit your config**
You'll probably need to change the external_server_address in your .{hotkey}.env file, to match the new server. Either use

```bash
vision create-config
```
Or
```bash
nano .{hotkey}.env
```
Replace with your hotkey name (use `ls -a` to see all files)

Then:

```bash
git fetch
git checkout production
git pull
. venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .
./launch_validators.sh
```

Wait for a few beats to see if that is working perfectly. If so, fantastic!

If you face any issues, you can always change your config back to use the old GPU (if it was on runpod, for example), and 
```bash
git checkout main
./launch_validators.sh
```

To revert back whilst you wait for GPU support.
